WorkItem.Description:
From thread:
http://www.codeplex.com/PHPExcel/Thread/View.aspx?ThreadId=41696
 
In PHPExcel_Reader_Excel5 and PHPExcel_Writer_Excel5, there is missing support for protected cells as when one uses $objWorksheet->protectCells().
 
Note, this is not the same as locking / unlocking cells although there are similarities. Instead, it corresponds to feature in MS Office Excel "Allow Users to Edit Ranges" (introduced in Excel 11 (2003))
 
See reference:
http://office.microsoft.com/en-us/excel/HA100968371033.aspx
WorkItem.Summary: Support for protectCells() in Excel5 reader/writer
